Blimey - I didn't realise so many people would remember me. I've been out of the emulation scene for a long while now, but tinkered around with various things in my own way. <br /><br /> '98 <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> - I do remember the C port being done (I`m afraid my memory is a bit poor), didn't realise it was you. I have to say the work you have done on bsnes is awesome. <br /><br /> As far as perfect digital - EDL is pure digital for now.<br /><br /> Anyway, I managed to put the correct timebases through and generate a new image - no more corruption in the colours, but I think i may still need to tweak something more <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />  <br /><br /><img src="http://savourysnax.github.com/EDL/images/nes_new.gif" alt="Image" /><br /><br /> Strangely I seem to have to knock the colour phase out by 4 cycles to get close to the correct colours (based on the NTSC timings on the wiki).<br /><br /> so colour burst is 8. colour from palette needs + 4 to its phase index. I need to have a think....<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5156">SavourySnaX</a> — Mon Jan 16, 2012 12:05 pm</p><hr />
