Interesting idea. I always wanted to see the NES simulated like that... The approach of emulating the individual chips is perfect for the NES because of the insane amount of mappers it uses... If each mapper is emulated as its own chip(s), we could easily add new ones without messing with the CPU and PPU.<br /><br />Sorry if I can't be of any help though... I'm not much of a hardware guy, and I certainly don't know anything about NTSC signals! =)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun Jan 15, 2012 12:10 pm</p><hr />
